On Tue, 28 Feb 2006, bill moon wrote:

> I have been using hylomar for sealing valve covers for several years and
> it has worked well for me. The only caveat is that it is not supposed to
> be stored at a temperature of over 100 degrees F.

> Has anyone noticed any changes in the stuff after storing at a very high
> temp?

I routinely leave my tube of hylomar in my bus through SoCal summers.  I
never noted any change in the stuff.  In fact, I've never heard of any
storage requirement, but then again it might have crept into the fine
print.

